  "benefit_assessment_plain_language": "M4w removes the duplicate warmup batch from the Flye proof path and moves CUDA context setup into a true external worker session. In the positive toy-raw run, Flye submitted only the actual request; the response was request ordinal 1 with CUDA context warm, no warmup JSONL or warmup output files were generated, and exact CPU artifacts still matched. The Flye-visible selected worker_process_ms fell to 14.157398 ms versus M4u 440.793131 ms and M4v 463.398560 ms. This is a real seam-level benefit, but it is still not an end-to-end Flye speedup: CPU toy-raw elapsed 73s and M4w elapsed 83s because the rest of Flye remains CPU-bound.",
